Mastercard revenue and profit top estimates
Mastercard posted higher-than-expected revenue and earnings per share for the first quarter due to an increase in transactions and volume growth on its network. The card network also reported an increase in expenses as it continues to invest in digital payment technology and security features to bring down fraud in the card space.

May. 2, 2017 at 10:35 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com









Synchrony Financial shares tumble after earnings
Synchrony Financial, one of the largest store credit-card issuers, reported earnings that fell and missed expectations, sending shares about 14% lower in morning trading Friday. The Stamford, Conn., company's results are the latest that will stir concern about the health of the consumer's balance sheet after a long period of growth and recovery from the 2008 financial crisis.

