Capital One has an impressive track record in the US credit card category, and is among the largest issuers, despite its highly specialised business model and lack of a national branch network. Nevertheless, more investment is needed and, among other things, a greater geographic spread and less focus on credit cards. The company is operating in an increasingly complex environment, with tougher regulation of banks and low interest rates.

